Good question Pack Mom,<br><br>
I am writing this before the morning brew (coffee) has finished percolating.(dripping through the filter)<br><br>
The times in my life that I have felt the most anger comes from feelings of abandonment and betrayal (lack of trust.)  That's true for all of us (vet and non vet) alike.  I believe you once wrote that you have three daughters.  Did one of your girls ever look at you and say &quot;but mom, I love him?&quot;  And what was your reaction.  Oh, I hope this guy is trustworthy.  I hopet he doesn't leave her hanging in the wind..&quot;   &quot;What can I do to protect her?&quot;  I'm sure we, as parents, could write volumes about our feelings.<br><br>
Abandonment and betrayal is certainly not unique to veterans although the results were certainly more devasting.  Most times, although not always, broken hearts repair a little easier than broken bodies and spirits.<br><br>
I, sometimes, (more than thrice) have asked myself why put yourself through the trauma of being vulnerable and trusting someone.  It's a basic need.  It challenges us to be more than what we are.  The major question is how to do it.<br><br>
There are major &quot;industries&quot; in our society on &quot;social contracts.&quot;  How to how a better relationship, etc. etc. etc.<br><br>
Didn't we all give advice to a woman (Beth, I think) on another thread.  I think Ed, said it best when he suggested a balance between support your mate and not losing yourself in the mud.<br><br>
I have a bumper sticker on the back of my car, which I think is funny.  SINCE I GAVE UP HOPE, I FEEL MUCH BETTER.<br><br>
I used to think that life could be so easy, another example of hope winning out over experience, and it can be with lots of work, or so I'm told.  I tell my daughter that the dramas of life are better suited outside the door of our home.  This is a place where we can take off our shoes and relax.<br><br>
Paul<br><br>
PS -- I guess I just said that feellings of abandonment and distrust are my triggering points, but then again I have to answer why I put myself in those positions.  I'm sure DR. ED, (my hero) can add some valuable insights into this one.  He started &quot;this thread&quot; a few threads back.
